.TH HIDLOOM-KEY 1 "@HIDLOOM_VERSION@" "HIDloom" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hidloom-key \- send key press, release, or tap events to logicd
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hidloom-key
[\fB--socket\fR \fIPATH\fR] [\fB--hold-us\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--gap-us\fR \fIN\fR]
.B tap
\fIKEYCHORD\fR [\fIKEYCHORD\fR...]
.br
.B hidloom-key
[\fB--socket\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.BR press | release
\fIKEYCHORD\fR|\fIKEY\fR [\fIMOD\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hidloom-key
connects to the logicd key event socket and emits binary synthetic key events.
It is intended for local smoke tests, scripts, and recovery actions.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --socket PATH
Unix socket path. The default is the logicd key event socket.
.TP
.B --hold-us N
Hold duration for tap events.
.TP
.B --gap-us N
Gap between tap events.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command help.
.SH KEY FORMAT
\fIKEYCHORD\fR is normally written as \fB0xMMKK\fR, where \fBMM\fR is the modifier
byte and \fBKK\fR is the HID keycode. A key without modifier may be written as
\fB0xKK\fR.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hidloom-keytext (1),
.BR hidloom-ctrl (1),
.BR logicd (8)
.br
